We first compute the two ratios step by step.

Step 1. Quick Ratio
• The quick ratio uses liquid current assets (excluding inventory). From the balance sheet we have:
 – Cash on Hand = 735892.55  
 – Bank Deposits = 103027.27  
 – Interest Receivable = 2566.71  
 – Accounts Receivable = 2923459.19  
• Quick Assets = 735892.55 + 103027.27 + 2566.71 + 2923459.19 = 3764945.72  
• Total Current Liabilities = 2736025.72  
• Quick Ratio = 3764945.72 / 2736025.72 ≈ 1.38

Step 2. Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, the Net Profit is –1669849.77 and Total Revenue is 6920513.79.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
 = (–1669849.77 / 6920513.79) × 100%  
 ≈ –24.13%

Thus, the final results are:

  "solution": {'Quick Ratio': '1.38', 'Net Profit Margin': '-24.13%'}
